### ============================================================
### Fiber Guardian API Test Suite
### 
### This file contains HTTP requests to test the API endpoints 
### of the compliance middleware. It requires the REST Client
### extension (or equivalent) for execution directly from the code editor.
### ============================================================

### Variables
@hostname = localhost
@port = 3000
@baseUrl = http://{{hostname}}:{{port}}/api

### ============================================================
### SECTION 1: SYSTEM HEALTH (controllers/systemController.js)
### ============================================================

### 1. Test Welcome Message (Redirected from root)
GET {{baseUrl}}/system/

### 2. Check Engine Status (Database Connection & OutreachAttempt ledger count)
GET {{baseUrl}}/system/status

### ============================================================
### SECTION 2: OUTREACH VALIDATION (POST /api/v1/outreach/validate)
### ============================================================

### 3. Validate Compliant Outreach (Expected: SEND)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8aaaa",
    "transcript": "Hello, this is a courtesy call regarding your recent statement.",
    "status": "PASSED",
    "aiReasoning": "Polite, compliant language. Within allowed timezone boundaries."
}

### 4. Validate Blocked Outreach - Harassment (Expected: BLOCK)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8aaaa",
    "transcript": "Pay your debt immediately or we will involve local law enforcement.",
    "status": "BLOCKED_CONTENT",
    "aiReasoning": "Blocked: Harassment. The phrase 'involve local law enforcement' falsely implies criminal proceedings for a civil debt."
}

### 5. Validate Blocked Outreach - Timezone Violation (Expected: BLOCK)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8aaaa",
    "transcript": "This is an automated text message regarding your balance.",
    "status": "BLOCKED_TIME",
    "aiReasoning": "Blocked: Timezone Violation. Local time for debtor is 10:15 PM. FDCPA regulates outreach strictly between 8 AM and 9 PM."
}

### ============================================================
### SECTION 3: ATTEMPT LEDGER (GET & DELETE /api/v1/attempts)
### ============================================================

### 6. Get ALL Logged Attempts (Ledger History)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts

### 7. Get ONLY Blocked Content Attempts (Filtered via Query Param)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts?status=BLOCKED_CONTENT

### 8. Soft Delete (Archive) an Attempt
### NOTE: Replace <ATTEMPT_ID> below with an actual _id dynamically generated from tests above
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts/<ATTEMPT_ID>

### ============================================================
### SECTION 4: DATA INTEGRITY TESTS (Mongoose Schema Defenses)
### ============================================================

### 9. Test Missing Debtor ID (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
### The Mongoose schema firmly requires the `debtorId` field.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "transcript": "This attempt is missing a debtor ID.",
    "status": "ERROR"
}

### 10. Test Invalid Status Enum Logic (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
### The `status` property only expects specific Enumerable values (e.g. BLOCKED_TIME).
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8aaaa",
    "transcript": "Invalid enum status payload.",
    "status": "RANDOM_UNAUTHORIZED_STATUS"
}

### ============================================================
### SECTION 5: ZERO-TRUST COMPLIANCE REFACTOR TESTS
### ============================================================

### 11. Test Malformed ObjectId in Archive Route (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
### Validates that the Mongoose isValidObjectId catches bad formatting 
### before attempting a database cast, preventing runtime exceptions.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts/malformed-id-123

### 12. Test NoSQL Injection Attempt on Filters (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
### Tests our rigorous defense against query parameter injection. Passing status[$ne]=ERROR
### will be rejected because the controller strictly bounds parameters as primitive strings.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts?status[$ne]=ERROR

### 13. Test Strict ENUM bounds on Filters (Expected: 400 Bad Request)
### Even if formatted structurally as a string, unrecognized payload states 
### will be intercepted before ever reaching the database layer.
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/attempts?status=UNKNOWN_FILTER_TYPE

### ============================================================
### SECTION 6: LUXON DETERMINISTIC TIMEZONE TESTS
### ============================================================

### 14. Test Missing Debtor Profile (Expected: 404 Not Found)
### The validate endpoint now explicitly verifies the debtor exists 
### before attempting to derive local timezone math.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8g9cc",
    "transcript": "Checking for missing profile.",
    "status": "PASSED"
}

### 15. Test Timezone Violation Dynamically
### NOTE: Requires a seeded DebtorProfile matching the ID below.
### If the server runs this exactly between 8 AM and 9 PM in the debtor's 
### strict timezone, it will evaluate to SEND. If executed outside those hours, 
### Luxon explicitly intercepts the request and safely forces a `BLOCKED_TIME`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/outreach/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "debtorId": "65e23f1a23b4c5d6e7f8aaaa",
    "transcript": "Hello, checking if you are currently within safe outreach hours.",
    "status": "PASSED"
}